  "upgrade_suggestion": "RKS/Sterling-cut current-release LP on cream transparent vinyl is already an audiophile-tier pressing of a 2024 album; no meaningful sonic upgrade exists. The Apple Music 'Deeper into the Well' deluxe edition (id 1758870783) adds 10 bonus tracks at lossy AAC quality but the source mix is the same.",
  "commentary": "Released March 15, 2024 by Interscope Records and MCA Nashville, *Deeper Well* is Kacey Musgraves' fifth studio album and a deliberate retreat from the synth-and-strings pop ambition of *Star-Crossed* (2021). Recorded primarily at Electric Lady Studios in New York with Daniel Tashian and Ian Fitchuk co-producing — the same team behind *Golden Hour* — the album leans on acoustic textures, slower tempos, and a meditative folk-influenced palette. Musgraves has framed it as a record about peace and slowing down, written largely after she moved out of Nashville and into a more rural setting.\n\nThe lead single *Deeper Well* and *Cardinal* anchor the album's emotional center — the former is a meditation on relationship boundaries (the well as a metaphor for needing more depth than circumstances allow), the latter is a song about a friend's passing. The whole record sits in a softer dynamic register than her earlier work; even the more upbeat tracks (*Heaven Is*, *Dinner with Friends*) avoid the shimmer of *Golden Hour*. *Deeper Well* won the Grammy for Best Country Album at the 2025 ceremony, Musgraves' second win in that category after *Golden Hour*.\n\nThe album's production design is intentionally low-resolution in a positive sense — lots of room sound, minimal stereo widening, vocals close to the listener with the band recorded as if in a single room. It's the album most often cited by Musgraves fans as her \"Sunday morning\" record.\n\n**About this 2024 Worldwide pressing (1×LP, Cream Transparent):** Interscope/MCA Nashville catalog `602455847041`. The lacquer was cut by **Ryan K. Smith at Sterling Sound** (`RKS STERLING` in the runout, with cut codes `276316E1` and `276316E2`). Smith is one of Sterling's senior cutters — his credits include extensive work on contemporary country, indie, and alternative releases. This makes three Sterling cuts in the collection: NFR Pallas (Joe Nino-Hernes / JN-H), Middle of Nowhere Whiskey LE (also JN-H), and Deeper Well (RKS) — Sterling Sound being the dominant cutting facility for current major-label vinyl on the US/EU market.\n\nThe Cream Transparent variant is the standard worldwide retail pressing — not a limited-edition color but the default vinyl color for this release. Other variants exist (Limited Edition versions r30109691 and r30104402, Picture Disc r30105227) with their own catnos. Comes in a gatefold jacket with a printed die-cut inner sleeve. Photographs in the gatefold were taken at The Farm & Fiddle in Florida, the property where Musgraves wrote much of the album.\n\n### Gemini Notes\n\nReleased in 2024, *Deeper Well* finds Kacey Musgraves exploring themes of self-care, boundaries, and emotional growth. Reunited with her *Golden Hour* co-producers, the album returns to a warm, acoustic-driven folk-pop sound.\n\n**About this pressing:**",
